We label the selection events by $U_A,U_B,U_C$ and the red‐ball event by $R$. 

1. The prior probability of choosing urn $U_i$ is 
$$
P(U_i)\;=\;\frac{c_i}{c_A+c_B+c_C}\,,\qquad i\in\{A,B,C\}\,. 
$$

2. Given urn $U_i$, the probability of drawing a red ball is 
$$
P(R\mid U_i)\;=\;\frac{r_i}{r_i+w_i}\,. 
$$

3. By the law of total probability, the probability of drawing a red ball is 
$$
P(R)\;=\;\sum_{i\in\{A,B,C\}}P(U_i)\,P(R\mid U_i)
\;=\;\frac{c_A}{c_A+c_B+c_C}\,\frac{r_A}{r_A+w_A}
+\frac{c_B}{c_A+c_B+c_C}\,\frac{r_B}{r_B+w_B}
+\frac{c_C}{c_A+c_B+c_C}\,\frac{r_C}{r_C+w_C}\,.
$$

4. By Bayes’ theorem, the posterior probability that the red ball came from urn $U_B$ is
$$
P(U_B\mid R)
\;=\;
\frac{P(U_B)\,P(R\mid U_B)}{P(R)}
\;=\;
\frac{\displaystyle\frac{c_B}{c_A+c_B+c_C}\,\frac{r_B}{r_B+w_B}}
{\displaystyle\frac{c_A}{c_A+c_B+c_C}\,\frac{r_A}{r_A+w_A}
+\frac{c_B}{c_A+c_B+c_C}\,\frac{r_B}{r_B+w_B}
+\frac{c_C}{c_A+c_B+c_C}\,\frac{r_C}{r_C+w_C}}\,.
$$

5. The common denominator $c_A+c_B+c_C$ cancels, yielding the final simplified form
$$
P(U_B\mid R)
=\frac{\displaystyle\frac{c_B\,r_B}{r_B+w_B}}
{\displaystyle\frac{c_A\,r_A}{r_A+w_A}
+\frac{c_B\,r_B}{r_B+w_B}
+\frac{c_C\,r_C}{r_C+w_C}}\,.
$$
